Another lame political quiz that a friend sent me shortly after seeing the thing in my last post.
You Are a New School Democrat

You like partying and politics - and are likely to be young and affluent. You're less religious, traditional, and uptight than most Democrats. Smoking pot, homosexuality, and gambling are all okay in your book. You prefer that the government help people take care of themselves.
What political persuasion are you?
Ok, but I hate saxophones, Clinton, Democrats, and US politics. Otherwise, right on target.

Back from the dead, just haven't had much to post about. This weekend was fun, chilled out with friends friday, did that gay-ass spanish cooking project with Brian, Tony, Pj, and Jeff on Sat, hung out with Will and Brett sunday, and today i went for a walk with Megan.

stuff's pretty good. friedman has started to annoy me, though i haven't annoyed him, he thinks well of me but i find some of what he says to be empty and without purpose. I'm sure i'm not alone.

now just sitting my lazy ass down to watch tv. i'm always leaving my AIM up, never putting on an away message, so it looks like i've been on for several consecutive hours. ew. so if you im me and i don't respond, i'm probably "doing something else" (no, no that)

later

It's almost the holidays. Accidentally forgot to hand in my movie review for my Facing History class, and I was planning to do that tomorrow.
Some asshat decides to compensate for his lack of balls by writing a bombthreat on a desk, so now all these people are disappointed over Winter Wonderland, and that just sucks. Otherwise, nothing different. Going upstate until Wed. or Tues. so I'll be back then. I might show up online, and my cell phone (521 9091) will be on.
That's all for now.

Max

Everyone was freezing outside then too. I also notice how chaotic the halls are becoming at the high school. I think that the high school is falling into total chaos, which is unbelievably cool. I decided to do one of those stupid things that describe yourself in your Livejournal, for the hell of it. Here goes. The Ultimate Politics Survey Describe your stance on: Abortion: I don't like it, but it would be foolish to make it illegal. So many women would get illegal abortions that there'd be way too many deaths. Affirmative Action: I think society should be colorblind. The person matters, not the ethnicity, race, etc. This is the only thing I'm kind of moderate on. Age of Consent: 16-18, whenever you feel is right. Animal Testing: If it gets cures, sure. Unnecessary pain inflicted on them is wrong though. Death Penalty: I don't care for murderers or rapists. There's a population problem already. Downloading Music/Movies: Don't care. Drug Decriminalization: Yes in terms of less dangerous drugs, definitely no to cocaine or heroine, etc. Factory Farming: Don't care. Free Trade: Bring this shit down. Now. Funding of Arts: If it makes society happy. Gay Marriage: I have no right to tell people who they can and can't love. Gun Control: As long as the owner is known to be a stable, law abiding citizen, it should be legal to own guns. Immigration: It's trouble causing. Hardcore Pornography: If you want to view it, go ahead. I'm not gonna tell you what to do. Human Cloning: If it is for the better, sure. Miltary Draft: No one has the right to send anyone else to die. Minimum Wage: Raise it, people need to live, not just get subsistence wages to keep them functioning. Prostitution: It keeps human nature in check. School Vouchers: Bad. Taxes: If it's for education, medicine, welfare, and other things that matter, let them go up. United Nations: A good step towards peace between nations, though the US still causes trouble. Universal Health Care: Necessary for any society. I don't want to have anything to do with any person who wants to make someone have to pay for their suffering/injuries. War on Terrorism: Great. Arrest/detain/exile Bush first. Welfare: Good, so noone has to starve. Take The Ultimate Politics Survey

I finally got a livejournal! So now you stalkers have something a little more tangible to look at. Maybe tangible isn't a good word to use but you know what I mean.
     So life is...static.
Nothing's happening, nothing good, nothing bad, just...nada.
So that's that, nothing new. SO EX-expletive-CITING!!!
     I'm in an indifferent mood really. Everyone's been telling me how they liked my article on "Why Americans Don't Vote" to tell the truth after these elections I don't even give an (expletive) about what happens. Go (expletive) yourselves, 58 million jackasses. 
     I'm also pretty sure the FBI is onto me. With those weird clicks on the phone, to those "wrong numbers" and other shit. So there. If I never post another entry it is probably because I'm in Guantanamo or Alcatraz. Send postcards.
     Another weird thing. I don't dream often, if ever. Lately I've been having seriously weird dreams, creeps me out. Sometimes it gets me so upset that in the morning I find myself drinking orange juice. That's so not me. Orange juice...
     You're probably thinking this is just another livejournal, but I wanted to make mine unique, because my nursery school teacher said I was special. So screw the rest of you. See my next entry.
